HEADWORD: Tridecatylene
<hw>Tri`de*cat"y*lene</hw>
<pr>(tr⟦isl⟧`d⟦esl⟧*k⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*l⟦emac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>tri-</ets>+ Gr. <grk>de`katos</grk> tenth + E.
eth<ets>ylene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A hydrocarbon,
<chform>C13H26</chform>, of the ethylene series, corresponding to
tridecane, and obtained from Burmah petroleum as a light colorless
liquid; -- called also <altname>tridecylene</altname>, and
<altname>tridecene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

